parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the APIM module can cause various electrical system malfunctions, leading to safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion on the battery terminals can cause electrical system failures, leading to safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the positive terminal
thick layer of blue corrosion on the positive terminal
and small holes at the base of the positive knob.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition and starting system can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle takes multiple attempts to start
the key can be removed from the ignition without the vehicle being in park
and the vehicle may not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission and Engine Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and engine control module can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: and the transmission is not in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System and Instrument Panel Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system and instrument panel can cause various malfunctions, leading to safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Dim or difficult-to-read instrument panel gauges
funny noise in the steering wheel when turning
and electric problems with lights taking a while to come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension toe links can cause uneven tire wear, affect vehicle handling, and potentially lead to loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: rear suspension feels unstable or loose
rear tires are out of alignment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Water Pump Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty design of the water pump can cause water to enter the engine oil, leading to engine failure, which can result in sudden loss of power, loss of steering and braking, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine shuts down while in motion

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and power loss can cause unexpected loss of speed, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially on high-speed roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Contamination
